caption: This photograph depicts a dead bird lying on a ground covered in what appears to be reddish-brown pine needles. The bird's body is centrally positioned in the image, with its wings spread out and feather details visible. The feathers are black with white spots, indicating it could be a common species of woodpecker. The background is uniformly covered with densely packed pine needles, providing a homogeneous texture throughout the photo. The image conveys a somber mood, emphasizing the stillness and finality of death in nature. The overall composition is simple, focusing on the contrast between the bird and its natural surroundings.
title: Squirrel returning to topsoil- dissintegrating in the duff of rotted, decaying and fresh needles on the forest floor.  Private forest preserve on green mountain, Washington, near Seattle.  From the environmental protection agencys project documerica, entheos.  "in praise of forests".  For additional images see fiche #s 209, 210, 211, 212, and 213.  Winter, 1974.
